= The Moscow Line Hardens

The <span style='color: #700000;'>KPD</span>’s party conference has concluded, and the outcome is a disaster for inter-party cooperation. The political atmosphere was toxic from the start. The formation of the hated <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span>, Chancellor Brüning's brutal austerity measures, and the SPD’s own internal chaos with the split of its left-wing have created the perfect storm for the hardliners. Any hope for the "Conciliator" faction was annihilated. In a series of ruthless political maneuvers orchestrated by Moscow, Ernst Thälmann has consolidated absolute power. The policy of branding the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> as "<span style="color: #c00000;">social fascists</span>" is no longer just a slogan; it is the unshakeable party line. Key figures of the conciliatory wing like Ernst Meyer have been publicly denounced and politically exiled.

The party is now a monolith, its strings pulled directly from the <span style="color: #D50000;">Comintern</span>. The immediate result is chaos within their own ranks.

